(10, 'Interon Beta 1B', 'Condyloma acuminata. Chronic active hepatitis B. Chronic hepatitis C. AIDS related Kaposis sarcoma. Hairy cell leukaemia. Melanoma. Chronic myeloid leukaemia. Follicular lymphoma. Carcinoid tumours. Multiple myeloma.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hepatic decompensation, autoimmune hepatitis or a history of autoimmune disease, immunosuppressed transplant recipients.', 'History of pulmonary disease (e.g. COPD) or DM prone to ketoacidosis. Coagulation disorders or severe myelosuppression. Monitor patients with history of MI and/or arrhythmic disorders. Psychiatric disorder, particularly depression. Poorly controlled thyroid dysfunction. Preexisting psoriasis. May impair ability to drive or operate machinery. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Flu like symptoms, alopecia, hypersensitivity reactions, nausea, anorexia, myelosuppression, lethargy, ocular side effects, depression, CV problems, nephrotoxicity, hypertriglyceridaemia, thyroid abnormalities, hyperglycaemia, psoriasiform rash, confusion, coma seizures. Hepatotoxicity, pulmonary infiltrates, pneumonitis and pneumonia, autoimmune diseases.'),
(11, 'Naproxen', 'Analgesic, antipyretic. Dysmenorrhoea. Rheumatoid arthritis, osteoarthritis. Musculo skeletal disorders. Post-partum and post operatively. Acute gout. Juvenile idiopathic arthritis. Acute migraine attacks.', 'Active Peptic ulcer, GI bleeding. Pregnancy and lactation. Hypersensitivity. Perioperative pain in the setting of CABG surgery.', 'Asthma, bleeding disorders, cardiovascular disease and those receiving coumarin anticoagulants. Aspirin/anti inflammatory induced allergy. Pre-existing CV, CHF, hypertension, GI disease, Hepatic impairment.', 'GI intolerance, rash, rarely jaundice, thrombocytopenia oedema. Vertigo, pruritus, ecchymosis, purpura, fluid retention, abdominal pain, constipation, heartburn, gross bleeding/perforation, abnormal renal function, haemolysis, hearing disturbances, dysponea.'),
(12, 'Urofollitrophin', 'Amenorrhoea and infertility. Hypogonadotrophic hypogonadism in males. Cryptorchism. To aid in vitro fertilization.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hormone dependent malignancies (prostate, breast). Pituitary or ovarian tumour. Prostate carcinoma or androgen dependent neoplasms. Ovarian dys-genesis, absent uterus. Premature menopause. Tubal occulusion.', 'Ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome - Polycystic ovary. Precocious puberty. fluid retention is males.', 'Allergic reactions, headache, mental depression, ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome, gynaecomastia, Pain in lower abdomen and even ovarian bleeding and shock can occur in females.'),
(13, 'Cefazolin', 'Respiratory tract infection, post operative chest infections, empyema and lung abscess. Urinary tract infections (pyelonephritis). Soft tissue, skin infection, infected gangrene, otitis media and mastoiditis, peritonitis and wound infections Septicaemia, whether gram-positive or gram-negative Endocarditis, gynaecological and obstetrical infection (septic abortion, uterine and neonatal infection, pelvic abscess). Gonorrhoea or syphills. Bone and joint infections (osteomyelitis and septic arthritis). Especially useful in billary tract infection.', 'Patients with known allergy to cephalosporin group. Pseudomembranous colitis. Use in premature and infants under one month of age.', 'Hypersensitivity to penicillins, impaired renal function.', 'GIT upsets, allergic reactions, depressed haematopoiesis, transient rise of SGPT, BUN, SGOT, Perineal pruritus, candidiasis, convulsions, eosinophilia, thrombocythemia.'),
(14, 'Amitriptyline', 'Depressive illness accompanied by anxiety, agitation, restlessness and disturbances of sleep. Masked depression, dysphoria and depression in alcoholics.', 'Ischaemic heart disease. Epilepsy. Narrow angle glaucoma. Cardiovascular insufficiency. Retention of urine, severe liver dysfunction. Pregnancy, lactation and children below the age of six years.', 'Hyperthyroidism, suicidal tendency in seriously depressed patients. Renal hepatic or cardiac disease. May activate latent schizophrenia. Ability to drive or operate heavy machinery may be impaired.', 'Dry mouth, constipation, epigastric distress, urinary retention, blurred vision, palpitation, sedation and mental confusion, fine tremors, seizure threshold is lowered. Postural hypotension.'),
