(161, 'Dimethindene Maleate', 'Antihistimine/antichlornergic orally and locally acting anti prulitic. Adjunct in the emergency treatment of anaphylactic shock.', 'Hypersensitivity, neonates.', 'Elderly, pylori, duodenal obstruction, angle-closure glaucoma, urinary retention, prostatic hyperplasia, epilepsy, renal and hepatic impairment. May affect performance of skilled tasks. BPH, bladder neck obstruction, hypertension. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'CNS depression, sedation, drowsiness, lassitude, dizziness. GI upsets, anorexia, or increased appetite, epigastric pain, blurring of vision, dysuria, dryness of mouth, tightness in chest, hypotension, muscular weakness, tinnitus, euphoria, headache, paradoxical CNS stimulation. CV collapse and respiratory failure.'),
(162, 'Cabergoline', 'Hyperprolactinemic disorders either idiopathic or due to pituitary adenomas.', 'Hypersensitivity to cabergoline or other ergot alkaloid. Uncontrolled hypertension.', 'Untreated hypertension or pregnancy induced hypertension (pre eclampsia and eclampsia), monitor LFTs).', 'Allergy, gastrointestinal intolerance, asthenia, fatique, flu like syndrome, malaise, hot flushes, edema, weight changes, somnolence, depression, nervousness, anxiety, impaired concentration, very rarely cardiac failure and constructive pericarditis, musculoskeletal pain, respiratory affection, abnormal vision, breast pain, dysmenorrhoea, decreased libido, overdose may produce nasal congestion, syncope or hallucinations.'),
(163, 'Beta Carotene', 'Vit A deficiency during infancy, pregnancy, lactation, heptatobillary disease, steatorrhea. Skin diseases like acne vulgaria, acne venenata, posiriasis, ichthyosis.', 'Acute eczema, rosacea, cuts, abrasions. Acute dermatitis. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Avoid exposure to sunlight, UV lamps. Avoid concomitant therapy with conventional acne, medical or cosmetic products. Regular use of liquid paraffin, long term oral neomycin use induces steatorrhea and interferes with Vit A absorption.', 'Feeling of warmth, stinging, excessive redness, oedema and crusting. Corneal opacities, dry eyes, visual disturbances, skeletal hyperostosis and musculoskeletal symptoms. Hair thinning, photosensitivity, changes in skin pigmentation, paronychia. GI disturbances, hepatitis.'),
(164, 'Lacidipine', 'Hypertension.', 'Within one month of MI, cardiogenic shock, unstable angina, aortic stenosis.', 'Use with caution in patient with poor cardiac reserve, pre-existing malfunctioning of the SA node/AV node, elderly and in patients with liver impairment. Use in lactating mothers only if benefit out weights the risk. if ischemic pain develops shortly after initiating lacidipine therapy should be withdrawn forthwith.', 'Headache, flushing, edema, dizziness and palpitations. Asthenia, rash, erythemaitching, gastric upset, polyuria, chest pain, gingival hyperplasia have been reported infrequently.'),
(165, 'Guar Gum', 'Adjuvant therapy in diabetes mellitus.', 'History of oesophageal disease or difficulty in swallowing. Not ingest as dry granules. Pregnancy, lactation and children.', 'Hypoglycaemia.', 'Nausea, feeling of fullness and loss of appetite, flatulence, diarrhoea and related gastro intestinal disturbances.'),
(166, 'Dihydroergotoxine (Codergocrine)', 'Primary progressive dementia. Arteriosclerotic dementia. Multi-infarct dementia. Alzheimers dementia.', 'Hypersensitivity to ingredients. Acute or chronic psychoses. contraindicated during pregnancy. Not recommended to paediatrics', 'Acute intermittent porphyria. Concomitent use of caffiene.', 'Headache, dizziness, nasal stuffiness, cramps, rashes, GI distubances.'),
(167, 'Folic Acid IP', 'Folate-deficient. Megaloblastic anaemia. Prophylaxis of megaloblastic anemia in pregnancy. Prophylaxis of neural tube defect in pregnancy. Malabsorption syndromes. Antiepileptic therapy.', 'Undiagnosed, megaloblastic anaemia, pernicious, aplastic or normocytic anaemias.', 'Treatment resistance may occur in patients with depressed haematopoiesis, alcoholism, deficiencies of other vitamins. Neonates.', 'Rarely hypersensitivity.'),
(168, '5 Aminosalicylic Acid', 'Mild to moderate ulcerative colitis and maintenance of remission.', 'Hypersensitivity. Severe hepatic or renal impairment. Children below the age of two years.', 'Elderly, active peptic ulcer, pregnancy, lactation, patients predisposed to pericarditis or myocariditis.', 'Headache, nausea, flu, fatigue, fever, rash, sore throat, diarrhoea, joint pain, dizziness, back pain, haemorrhoids, itching, hair loss, intolerance syndrome, peripheral oedema, pancreatitis, nephritis, hepatitis, lupus like syndrome.'),
(169, 'Mepacrine', 'Drug resistant Falciparum Malaria (but not being used due to its toxicity). Giardia Tapeworms.', 'Psoriasis.', 'Hepatic impairment.', 'Dizziness, gastrointestinal disturbances, yellow discoloration of skin may occur.'),
