(233, 'Vit D', 'Managing hypocalcemia in patients undergoing dialysia for chronic renal failure. Renal osteodystrophy. Hypocalaemia and Hyperphosphataemia. Vitamin D dependent rickets, renal tubular osteomalacia.', 'Hypercalcemia, evidence of Vitamin D toxicity, malabsorption syndrome, hypervitaminosis D, abnormal sensitivity to the effects of Vitamin D, decreased renal function. Contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation.', 'Pediatric doses must be individualized and monitored under close medical supervision, Idiopathic hypercalcemia, renal function impairment. Coronary disease renal function impairment and arteriosclerois, especially in the elderly. Hypoparathyroidism.', 'Dry mouth, muscle pain, polydipsia, anorexia, reversible azotemia, vomiting, pancreatitis, mild acidosis, metallic taste, rhinorrhea.'),
(234, 'Vit A', 'Vit A deficiency during infancy, pregnancy, lactation, heptatobillary disease, steatorrhea. Skin diseases like acne vulgaria, acne venenata, posiriasis, ichthyosis.', 'Acute eczema, rosacea, cuts, abrasions. Acute dermatitis. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Avoid exposure to sunlight, UV lamps. Avoid concomitant therapy with conventional acne, medical or cosmetic products. Regular use of liquid paraffin, long term oral neomycin use induces steatorrhea and interferes with Vit A absorption.', 'Feeling of warmth, stinging, excessive redness, oedema and crusting. Corneal opacities, dry eyes, visual disturbances, skeletal hyperostosis and musculoskeletal symptoms. Hair thinning, photosensitivity, changes in skin pigmentation, paronychia. GI disturbances, hepatitis.'),
(235, 'Heparin', 'Venous thromboembolism. Prophylaxis of postoperative VTE including during pregnancy with a history of deep-vein thrombosis or pulmonary embolism. Prevention of mural thrombosis. Acute peripheral arterial embolism, unstable angina. Venous thromboembolism.', 'Bleeding disorders, thrombocytopenia, severe hypotension, threatened abortion, piles, G.I. ulcers. Sub acute bacterial endocarditis, large malignancies, tuberculosis. Ocular and neurosurgery, lumbar puncture. Chronic alcoholics. Aspirin and other anti platelet drugs. Do not apply to bleeding areas or eyes. Patch test for tolerance before use on chronic open lesions. Severe renal and hepatic impairment. Cerebral or subarachnoid haemorrhage.', 'Renal or hepatic impairment. Not for systemic use or application to mucus membranes. Discontinue treatment if thrombocytopenia occurs. Hypersensitivity, elderly.', 'Bleeding due to overdose. Transient and reversible alopecia. Osteoporosis. Hypersensitivity reactions include urticaria, conjunctivitis, rhinitis, asthma, angioedema and anaphylactic shock, priapism. Bleeding, rash, aching bones, thrombocytopenia, alopecia, anaphylaxis, rigor, slight haematuria.'),
