(238, 'Amoxapine', 'Endogenous depression. Obsessive compulsive neurosis and phobic states.', 'Hypersensitivity. Renal, hepatic, cardiac insufficiency. Concurrent treatment with MAOIs. Mania, severe liver disease. Contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation. Contraindicated to paediatrics.', 'Recovery after MI, elderly CVS disease, liver impairment, epilepsy, psychosis. Increased intraocular pressure, history of urinary retention, alcohol. Avoid abrupt withdrawal.', 'Postural hypotension, dry mouth, blurring of vision, constipation, urinary retention, fatigue, dizziness, weakness, tremors, headache, confusion and delirium in elderly, weight gain, tardive dyskinesia, neuroleptic malignant syndrome, sexual disturbances. Agranulocytosis, thrombocytopenia, cardiac arrhythmias.'),
(239, 'Somatostatin', 'Bleeding oesophageal varices. Bleeding from gastric/duodenal ulcers and haemorrhagic gastritis. Intestinal and pancreatic fistulae. Hypersecretory endocrine tumours of the intestinal tract. To reduce complications after pancreatic surgery. Adjuvant value in diabetic ketoacidosis. Use in acromegaly is limited.', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Blood glucose levels must be monitored, particularly in diabetics. In patients with fistula taper the dose after closure of the fistulae.', 'Abdominal discomfort, flushing, nausea and bradycardia, stetorrhea, dyspepsia, hypochlorhydria, cholelithiasis, mild watery diarrhoea..'),
