(302, 'Follicle Stimulating Hormone (FSH)', 'Amenorrhoea and infertility. Hypogonadotrophic hypogonadism in males. Cryptorchism. To aid in vitro fertilization.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hormone dependent malignancies (prostate, breast). Pituitary or ovarian tumour. Prostate carcinoma or androgen dependent neoplasms. Ovarian dys-genesis, absent uterus. Premature menopause. Tubal occulusion.', 'Ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome - Polycystic ovary. Precocious puberty. fluid retention is males.', 'Allergic reactions, headache, mental depression, ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome, gynaecomastia, Pain in lower abdomen and even ovarian bleeding and shock can occur in females.'),
(303, 'Norfloxacin', 'Uro-genital infections. Typhoid fever. Acute bacterial gastroenteritis. Chronic bacterial prostatitis. Gonorrhoea, Prophylaxis of sepsis in neutropenic patients. Eye and ear infections.', 'Hypersensitivity. Pregnancy, lactation and children. History of epilepsy.', 'Renal insufficiency. Myasthaenia gravis. QT prolongation.', 'Headache, dizziness, rash, heart burn, abdominal cramps, diarrhoea, anorexia, sleep disturbances, anxiety, irritability, phototoxicity, rash, fever, arthralgia. Marrow depression. May precipitate epilepsy.'),
(304, 'Hydrocortisone', 'Replacement therapy: Adrenal insufficiency. Adrenogenital syndrome. Nonendocrine diseases: Rheumatoid arthirits. Osteoarthritis, Acute gouty arthirits. Collagen diseases e.g. systemic lupus erythematosus, polyarteritis nodosa, dermatomyositis, nephritic syndrome, glomerulonephritis and related diseases. Severe allergic reactions e.g. anaphylaxis, angioneurotic edema, urticaria and serum sickness and related diseases. Autoimmune diseases e.g. haemolytic anaemia, idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura, active chronic hepatitis and related diseases. Other lung diseases e.g. pulmonary edema, accelerate lung maturation and surfactant production in the foetus and prevent respiratory distress syndrome at birth. Infective diseases e.g. severe forms of tuberculosis, severe lepra reaction, certain forms of bacterial meningitis and Pneumocystis carinii pneumonia with hypoxia in AIDS patients along with proper antibiotic cover. Eye diseases e.g. inflammatory ocular diseases, allergic conjunctivitis, iritis, iridocyclitis, keratitis, retinitis, optic neuritis, uveitis. Skin diseases e.g. eczematous skin diseases. Pemphigus vulgaris, exfoliative dermatitis, Stevens Johnson syndrome. Intestinal diseases e.g. ulcerative colitis, Crohns disease, coeliac disease are chronic inflammatory intestinal diseases. Cerebral edema. Malignancies e.g. Acute lymphatic leukaemia, Hodgkins and other lymphomas. Hormone responsive breast carcinoma. Organ transplantation and skin allograft. Septic shock. Thyroid storm.', 'Viral, fungal, tuberculous or purulent infections unless until treated with proper antibiotic concurrently. Pregnancy. New born babies, premature infants or children below the age of five years. Peptic ulcer. Psychosis. Epilepsy. Renal failure. Osteoporosis. In ophthalmology, herps zoster, herpetic or fungal xeratitis, previous history of cataract.', 'Prolong use. CHF, hypertension, DM. Elderly and lactation.', 'Cushings habitus. Peptic ulceration may be aggravated. Sodium and fluid retention. Potassium and Calcium depletion. Muscle wasting, osteoporosis. GI disturbances and bleeding. Increased appetite and delayed wound healing. Bruising, striae, hirsutism, acne, flushing. Headache, depression, psychosis, menstrual irregularity. Suppression of pitutary-adrenocortical system. Dermal atrophy. Hyperglycaemia. Susceptibility to infection. Osteoporosis. Growth retardation. Foetal abnormalities. Topical application to the eye can produce corneal ulcers, raised IOP, reduced visual function and posterior subcapsular cataract.'),
(305, 'Losartan Potassium', 'Mild to moderate hypertension. Diabetic nephropathy in type 2 diabetes mellitus.', 'Hypersensitivity. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Volume-depleted patients including patients on diuretics and salt restriction, renal artery stenosis, elderly, renal or hepatic impairment.', 'Diarrhoea, dyspepsia, myalgia, oedema, dizziness and headache. Asthenia/fatigue, 1st dose hypotension, rash, angioedema, elevation of liver enzymes, impaired renal function, hyperkalaemia.');
INSERT INTO `patientModule` (`Id`, `DrugName`, `Indication`, `ContraIndication`, `Caution`, `SideEffects`) VALUES
(306, 'Diabasic Calcium Phosphate', 'Calcium supplements are usually required where dietary calcium intake is deficient. This dietary requirement varies with age and is relatively greater in childhood, pregnancy and lactation due to an increased demand. Calcium supplement is also required in paused menopausal women and persons with osteopenia specially after the age of 60 years.', 'Patients with Calculi renal calculi or history of renal calculi; hypercalcaemia; hypophosphataemia.', 'Renal impairment, hypercalcaemia-associated disease eg. other malignancies; sarcoidosis; elderly.', 'Co-administration with thiazide diuretics or Vit D may lead to milk alkali syndrome and hypercalcaemia. Decreased absorption with coricosteroids. Decreases absorption of tetracyclinea, atenolol, iron, quinolones, alendronate, Na fluoride, Zn and calcium-channel blockers. Enhances cardiac effects of digitialis glycosides and may precipitate digitalis intoxication.'),
(307, 'Xipamide', 'Oedema.', 'Hypersensitivity. Severe renal impairment. Severe electrolyte impairment. Precomatose states associated with cirrhosis. Lactation. Untreated Addisons disease.', 'Avoid administration during Ist trimester of pregnancy. Renal or hepatic dysfunction. Diabetes mellitus, gout, prostatic hypertrophy. Prostatic hyperplegia. Elderly.', 'Weakness, fatigue, muscle cramps, cardiac arrhythmias. Hypokalemia. Hyponatremia. G.I. disturbances. Hearing loss. Hyperuricaemia, nocturia, dizzines, impauired glucose metabolism.'),
(308, 'Ceftazidime', 'Serious infections of the respiratory tract, ENT, skin, soft tissue, bone and joints, billary and GI tract, UTI, septicaemia, meningitis. Infections in immunocompromised patients.', 'Hypersensitivity to Penicillins or Cephalosporins.', 'Neonates and infants, renal or hepatic impairment, prolong use.', 'GI disorders, Pseudomembranous colitis, candidiasis, eosinophilia, neutropenia, leukopenia, thrombocytopenia, rise in liver enzymes and blood urea. Pain at injection site.'),
(309, 'Insulin (Human) Ultralente', 'Produced by Recombinant technology or, enzymatic modification of procaine insulin. Insulin analogues. Type I DM. Type II DM not controlled by oral drugs. Diabetic ketoacidosis (Diabetic coma). Hyperosmolar (nonketotic hyperglycaemic coma). During septecemia or surgical procedures.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hypoglycaemia and insulinoma.', 'Renal impairment. Ischemic heart disease. Combination therapy. Insulin resistance.', 'Hypoglycaemia, development of antibodies to insulin, hypersensitivity, local Lipodystrophy (very rare), Oedema. Local reaction at injection site.'),
(310, 'Iron (III) Hydroxide Polymaltose', 'Iron deficiency either due to chronic blood loss or poor absorption.', 'Iron intolerance.', 'History peptic ulcer, severe renal failure. Iron and tetracycline bind together leading to impairment of absorption.', 'GI upset, black stools, abdominal discomfort or pain by oral therapy.'),
(311, 'Mycophenolate Mofetil', 'Prophylaxis of renal or cardiac graft rejection.', 'Hypersensitivity. Pregnancy and lactation. Rare hereditary deficiency of hypoxanthine-guanine phosphoribosyltransferase (HGPRT), including Kelley-Seegmiller or Lesch-Nyhan syndrome.', 'Active serious GI disease. Instruct patients with increased risk of skin cancer to limit sunlight exposure and use sunscreen. Neutropenia. Active peptic ulcer disease. Severe renal impairment.', 'Diarrhoea. Leukopenia. Super added bacterial, viral or fungal infections. Possible development of lymphoma. Vomiting, GI haemorrhage and perforation, acne, rash, alopecia, dizziness, pancreatitis, hepatitis, pulmonary fibrosis.'),
(312, 'Recombinant LH', 'Amenorrhoea and infertility. Hypogonadotrophic hypogonadism in males. Cryptorchism. To aid in vitro fertilization.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hormone dependent malignancies (prostate, breast). Pituitary or ovarian tumour. Prostate carcinoma or androgen dependent neoplasms. Ovarian dys-genesis, absent uterus. Premature menopause. Tubal occulusion.', 'Ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome - Polycystic ovary. Precocious puberty. fluid retention is males.', 'Allergic reactions, headache, mental depression, ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome, gynaecomastia, Pain in lower abdomen and even ovarian bleeding and shock can occur in females.'),
(313, 'Doxycycline Monohydrate', 'Respiratory, genito-urinary, dental, ophthalmic, ENT and gynaecological infections. Venereal diseases.', 'Hypersensitivity. Lactation.', 'Impaired hepatic function, blood dyscrasias. Antacids, mineral supplements.', 'Tooth discoloration, enamel hypoplasia, reduced fibula growth rate. Avoid use in children below eight years, unless no alternative drug.'),
(314, 'Amiodarone', 'Tachyarrhythmias associated with W.P.M. symdrome, atrial flutter and fibrillation, paroxysmal tachyarrhythmias not responding to other agents.', 'Bradycardia, A.V. block, goitre.', 'Pregnancy, lactation, cardiac failure, monitor thyroid and hepatic functions, hypothyroidism, renal disorders, eye disease.', 'G.I upsets, microdeposits in cornea, photosensitization, pulmonary alveolitis, hepatic and neurological effects.'),
(315, 'Codeine', 'Mild to moderate pain; diarrhoea ; cough suppression', 'Acute respiratory depression, paralytic ileus, conditions associated with raised intracranial pressure and head injury and convulsive disorders. Alcoholisms. Pregnancy.', 'Hypothyroidism, adrenocortical insufficiency, asthma, impaired hepatic or renal function, prostatic hyperplasia, hypotension, shock, inflammatory or obstructive bowel disorders, myasthenia gravis. Infants, neonates. Rdduce dose in elderly or debilitated patients. May impair ability drive or operate machinery. Lactation.', 'Constipation.'),
(316, 'Spironolactone', 'Hypertension. Oedema. Due to CCF. Hepatic cirrhosis or nephrotic syndrome. Hypokalaemia.', 'Anuria. Hyperkalaemia. Severe or progressive renal failure. Lactation. Addisons disease.', 'Hepatic impairment. Diabetes Mellitus. Elderly and pregnancy.', 'Headache, drowsiness, mental confusion, rash, gynaecomastia, G.I. upset. Electrolyte imbalance. menstrual irregularities. Loss of libido and impotence. Agranulocytosis.'),
(317, 'Ginkgo Biloba', 'Cerebrovascular and peripheral activator. Dementia.', 'Hypersensitivity. Acute phase of cerebrovascular, accidents, acute myocardial infarction, hypotension. Pregnancy and children.', 'Patients receiving anticoagulants or drug tht may affect platelet aggregation.', 'Headache, dizziness, palpitations, GI disturbances, bleeding disorders, skin hypersensitivity reactions.'),
(318, 'Phenindione', 'Venous thrombosis, pulmonary embolism, atrial fibrillation with embolisation.', 'Hepatic or renal impairment. History of peptic ulcer. Cerebrovascular haemorrhage. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Hypertension. Elderly. Severe infections. Vit K deficiency.', 'Rash, fever, diarrhoea, alopecia, agranulocytosis, hepatitis. Orange urine, leukopenia, nephropathy. DUE TO ITS TOXIC EFFECTS NOT BEING USED NOW A DAYS.'),
(319, 'Bupivacaine', 'Infiltration, block, caudal, epidural, lumbor, anaesthesia with long duration of action.', 'Hypersensitivity. Lactation.', 'Cardiovascular diseases. Elderly debilitated patients. Shock. Hepatic impairment.', 'CNS depression. Respiratotry apnoea. Hypotension. Bradycardia and arrhythmias. Persistent neurological deficits despite anaesthetic recovery. Allergy/angioneurotic oedema. Methemoglobinaemia. Seizures.'),
(320, 'Polydimethyl Siloxane', 'GI tract: To relieve flatulence, to prevent gastroesophageal reflux. Eye (as silicon oil): Retinal detachments and contact lenses. medical devices to elastomers, rhampoos. Topical use for prevention, maceration and excoriation of skin, bedsores, ulcers and burns. Use in medical devices to elastomers, rhampoos.', 'Topical Use - Hypersensitivity.', 'Infantile colic.', 'Eye: Cataract, corneal decompensation, glaucoma, pupillary block, keratopathy iritis and endophthalmitis. Topical use: Itching, burning, sensation and rashes.'),
(321, 'Antithymocyte Ig', 'Prevention and treatment of acute rejection in organ transplantation and therapy of aplastic anaemia.', 'Pregnancy and breast feeding, getriactic patients. Hypersensitivity.', 'Regular monitoring of blood count and T cell count.', 'High fever, chills and vigor during administration.'),
(322, 'Fluconazole IP', 'Superficial mucosal candidiasis. Candidal balanitis, vaginal candidiasis. Dermatophytosis, pityriasis, versicolor and candida infections. Cryptococcal infections including meningitis, systemic candidasis. Prevention of relapse following a primary course of antifungal treatment for acute cryptococcal infections in patients with aids. Prophylaxis of fungal infections in immunocompromised patients.', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Renal or hepatic impairment. May prolong QT interval. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Nausea, headache, skin rash, abdominal pain, vomiting and diarrhoea. Elevated liver function values, rash, exfoliative. Rarely angioedema, anaphylactic reactions and thrombocytopenia. Hepatotoxicity, rarely anaphylaxis. Stevens-Johnson syndrome.'),
(323, 'Clopidogrel bisuirate', 'Reduction of athero-sclerotic events (MI, stroke, and vascular death) in patients with atherosclerosis documented by recent stroke, recent MI or established peripheral arterial disease.', 'Hypersensitivity, peptic ulcer or intracranial haemorrhage.', 'Patients at risk of increased bleeding from trauma, surgery, hepatic impairment.', 'Neutropenia, thrombotic thrombocytopenic, purpura, diarrhoea, rash pruritus and abdominal discomfort.'),
(324, 'Sulphadiazine', 'Infections caused by Strepto. pyogenes, Haemophilus influenzae, H.ducreyi, Calymmatobacterium granulomatis, Vibrio cholerae. Only a few Staph. aureus, gonococci, meningococci, pneumococci, Escherichia coli and shiegella. Chlamydiae. Actinomyces, Nocardia and Toxoplasma.', 'Hypersensitivity. Folate deficiency or hyperkalaemia. G6PD deficiency.', 'Pregnancy and lactation. Renal impairment.', 'Crystalluria. Anaphylactic reactions.'),
(325, 'Mebendazole', 'Round worm, hookworm, whipworm, mixed infestations, threadworm and tapeworm.', 'Pregnancy.', 'Lactation. Expulsion of Ascaris from mouth or nose may occur.', 'Diarrhoea, nausea, abdominal pain, allergic reactions, loss of hair and granulocytopenia with high doses.'),
(326, 'Fluorometholone USP', 'Treatment of corticosteroid responsive inflammation of the palpebral and bulbar conjunctiva, cornea and anterior segment of the eye.', 'Viral diseases of the cornea and conjunctiva, including epithelial herps simplex keratitis, vaccinia, varicella and also in mycobacterial infection of ocular structures. Pregnancy, lactation and below the age of two years.', 'Glaucoma (check intraocular pressure periodically), history of herpes simplex fungal or bacterial infections. Not to be used in mustard gas keratitis and Sjogrens keratoconjunctivitis. May cause corneal and scleral thinning which may lead to perforation in serious cases. Use of steroids after cataract surgery may prolong healing time and increase bleb formation.', 'Elevation of intraocular pressure with possibility of glaucoma and infrequent optic nerve damage, posterior subcapsular cataract formation and delayed wound healing.'),
(327, 'Cisplatin', 'Metastatic testicular and ovarian carcinoma, advanced bladder, head and neck cancer.', 'Hypersensitivity. Renal impairment. Pregnancy, lactation and children. The risk of hearing loss is increased.', 'Maintain good hydration. Shock like state sometimes occurs during IV infusion. Monitor haemotological, neurological status and renal functions. Hypomagnesaemia. Hypocalcaemia. Hyperuricaemia.', 'Nausea, vomiting, tinnitus, deafness, neuropathy, nephrotoxicity, electrolyte imbalance.'),
(328, 'Formoterol', 'Acute attacks of bronchospasm, reversible airways obstructions.', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Thyrtoxicosis; severe CV disorders e.g. ischaemic heart disease, tachyarrhythmias or severe heart burn; prolonged QT interval. DM; pregnancy, lactation; child <5 years do not initiate or increase the dose during an exacerbation. May produce paradoxical bronchospasm.', 'Tremor, headache, tiredness, restlessness, dizziness, dry mouth.'),
(329, 'Chloramphenicol', 'Enteric fever (Typhoid and Para typhoid). H.Influenzae meningitis. Anaerobic infections, intraocular infections, urinary tract infections, conjunctivitis, external ear infections. Corneal ulcer, bacterial conjunctivitis, trachoma, ocular infections. Otitis externa, chronic otitis media. Pre and post antral or mastoid surgery.', 'Hypersensitivity, trivial infections or prophylaxis, concomitant use of penicillins. Large doses in neonates, bone marrow hypoplasia. Contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation.', 'Never use in minor infections or those of undefined etiology. Avoid repeated courses. Concomitant use of anti coagulants, and convulsants, sulphonylurea. Hazard of aplastic anaemia is very unlikely but should be borne in mind while assessing the benefit expected from their use. Application should be discontinued if allergic reaction occurs.', 'GI upsets, optic and peripheral neurites, dry mouth, allergic skin reactions. Gray baby syndrome, supra infections. Bone marrow depression, aplastic anaemia, agranulocytosis, thrombocytopenia or pancytopenia. Hypersensitivity reactions, irritation.'),
(330, 'Celiprolol', 'Hypertension. Angina pectoris. Safer in asthmatics.', 'Hypersensitivity. Sinus bradycardia. 1st degree heart block, cardiogenic shock, uncompensated heart failure, hypotension. Pregnancy (2nd & 3rd trimesters).', 'Lactation.', 'Nausea, diarhhoea, abdominal discomfort, headache, fatigue, dizziness, insomnia.'),
(331, 'Nandrolone Phenyl Decanoate', 'Synthetic androgens with higher anabolic and lower androgenic activity. Catabolic states. Renal insufficiency. Osteoporosis. Suboptimal growth in boys. Hypoplastic, haemolytic and malignancy associated anaemia. To enhance physical ability in atheletes. Metastatic breast cancer.', 'Prostatic or breast carcinoma (male). Liver disease, nephrosis, porphyria. Infants, pregnancy and lactation. Patients who may be adversely affected by fluid retention - such as CHF, epilepsy, migraine.', 'Diabetic patients. Hepatic impairment. Elderly. Discontinue if signs of virilisation in women occur.', 'Male: Postpuberal, Acne, gyanecomastia, bladder, irritability, priapism, insomnia, chills, decreased libido, hepatic dysfunction, nausea, diarrhoea, prostatic hyperplasia. Acne, virilism, chills, insomnia, hyperpigmentation, diarrhoea, nausea. Female, Virilism, hypercalcaemia, nausea, diarrhoea, chills, insomnia, Iron deficiency anaemia, hepatic dysfunction. OXYMETHOLONE, STANOZOLOL CAN PRODUCE JAUNDICE AND WORSEN LIPID PROFILE.'),
(332, 'Budesonide', 'Prophylaxis of asthma', 'Hypersensitivity. Acute infections uncontrolled by antimicrobial chemotherapy. Contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation.', 'Active or doubtfully quiescent tuberculosis, paradoxical bronchospasm; children, elderly.', 'Loss of skin collagen and SC atrophy; local hypopigmentation of deeply pigmented skin; dryness, irritation, epistaxis, rarely ulceration or perforation of the nasal septum; smell and taste disturbances; hoarseness and candidiasis of the mouth or throat.'),
(333, 'Sotalol', 'Supraventricular and ventricular arrhythmias.', 'Obstructive airways disease, sinus bradycardia cardiogenic shock, 2nd and 3rd degree AV block, uncontrolled cardiac failure, metabolic acidosis, hypotension, severe peripheral arterial disease.', 'Pregnancy and lactation. Renal insufficiency, preexisting sick sinus syndrome.', 'Nausea, sleep disorders, lassitude, diarrhoea, palpitations, bradycardia, weakness, dyspnoea, decreased sexual activity, impotence, extremity pain, back pain, asthma, visual disturbances, cardiac arrhythmias. May mask the symptoms of hyperthyroidism and of hypoglycaemia. May unmask myasthenia gravis. May worsen psoriasis.'),
(334, 'Bisoprolol', 'Hypertension. Coronary artery disease.', 'Bradycardia, second or third degree heart block, conduction abnormalities, congestive heart failure, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, peripheral vascular insufficiency pregnancy and lactation.', 'Poor L.V. function, bronchial asthma, diabetes, thyrotoxicosis, M.I, severe renal impairment, abrupt withdrawal.', 'Giddiness, headache, fatigue, bradycardia, nausea, dyspnoea, sleep disturbances, cold extremities, reduced libido.'),
(335, 'Alprazolam', 'Mild depression. Panic disorders. Anxiety associated with depression.', 'Hypersensitivity. Acute narrow angle glaucoma. Pregnancy, lactation and children. Prex existing CNS depression or coma, respiratory depression, acute pulmonary insufficiency or sleep apnoea, severe hepatic impairment.', 'Concomitant administration of CNS depressants. May impair ability to drive or operate macninery.', 'Drowsiness or light headedness, withdrawal seizures, anorexia, transient amnesia or memory impairment, loss of coordination, slurred speech, musculo skeletal weakness, pruritus. Ataxia, confusion and depression.'),
(336, 'Clozapine', 'In patients non responsive or intolerant to conventional antipsychotics.', 'In patients with history of drug induced granulocytopaenia/agranulocytosis/myeloproliferative disorders, alcoholics and toxic psychosis, drug intoxication, comatose conditions and other forms of CNS depression. Contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation. Not recommended to paediatrics.', 'Before and during the treatment, blood counts must be done regularly. Treatment should be started only WBC is more than 3500/cmm and absolute neutrophil count is more than 2000/cmm.', 'Drowsiness, fatique, hypersalivation, dizziness, headache, neutropenia leading to agranulocytosis.'),
(337, 'Nadrolone Phenylpropionate', 'Synthetic androgens with higher anabolic and lower androgenic activity. Catabolic states. Renal insufficiency. Osteoporosis. Suboptimal growth in boys. Hypoplastic, haemolytic and malignancy associated anaemia. To enhance physical ability in atheletes. Metastatic breast cancer.', 'Prostatic or breast carcinoma (male). Liver disease, nephrosis, porphyria. Infants, pregnancy and lactation. Patients who may be adversely affected by fluid retention - such as CHF, epilepsy, migraine.', 'Diabetic patients. Hepatic impairment. Elderly. Discontinue if signs of virilisation in women occur.', 'Male: Postpuberal, Acne, gyanecomastia, bladder, irritability, priapism, insomnia, chills, decreased libido, hepatic dysfunction, nausea, diarrhoea, prostatic hyperplasia. Acne, virilism, chills, insomnia, hyperpigmentation, diarrhoea, nausea. Female, Virilism, hypercalcaemia, nausea, diarrhoea, chills, insomnia, Iron deficiency anaemia, hepatic dysfunction. OXYMETHOLONE, STANOZOLOL CAN PRODUCE JAUNDICE AND WORSEN LIPID PROFILE.'),
(338, 'Dimenhydrinate', 'Prevention and treatment of motion sickness. Nausea and vertigo cause by menieres disease.', 'Hypersensitivity. Porphyria Lactation. Contraindicated below the age of two years.', 'Angle-closure glaucoma, urinary retention, prostatic hyperplasia, pyloroduodenal obstruction, epilepsy. Elderly. Tasks requiring mental.', 'Sedation, dry mouth, thickened resp tract secretions, tightness of chest, bradycardia followed by tachycardia and arrhythmias, blurred vision urinary retention, constipation, GI disturbance, blood dyscrasias. Paradoxical CNS stimulation may occur in child and occasionally in adults.'),
(339, 'Sucralfate', 'Duodenal and gastric ulcer. Chronic gastritis.', 'Severe renal dysfunction, hypophosphataemia.', 'Antacids should not be taken along with Sucralfate. To be taken one hour before the major meal.', 'Dry mouth, nausea, constipation.'),
(340, 'Fenoverine', 'Antispasmodic.', 'Pregnancy, lactation, hypersensitivity, chronic liver or renal disease. Hyper thermia during or after anesthesia or exercise.', 'Hepatic or renal insufficiency, elderly persons. Unexplained muscle pain. Myopathy.', 'Myalgia, reversible rhabdomyolysis, dyspepsia.'),
(341, 'Betamethasone Valerate', 'Atopic eczema. Allergic contact dermatitis. Lichen simplex. Primary irritant dermatitis. Seborrheic dermatitis. Psoriasis of face, flexures. Varicose eczema. Cystic acne. Alopecia areata. Discoid LE. Hypertrophied scars, keloids. Lichen planus. Nail disorders. Psoriasis of palm, sole, elbow, knee. A combination of steroid with proper antibiotic cover may also be used for: Impetigo, furunculosis, secondary infected dermatoses, napkin rash, otitis externa, intertriginous eruptions.', 'Hypersensitivity. Rosacea or perioral dermatitis. Primary infective skin. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Infants. Secondary dermatological infections.', 'Thinning of epidermis. Dermal changes - atrophy. Telangiectasia, Striae. Easy bruising, Hypopigmentation. Delayed wound healing. Fungal and bacterial infections. Systemic adverse effects of topical steroids on prolong use: Adrenal pituitary suppression. Cushings syndrome.'),
(342, 'Lafutidine', 'Gastric and duodenal ulcers.', 'Severe renal and hepatic impairment.', 'Early hepatic and renal impairment. Elderly and lactation.', 'Anaphylactic reactions, blood dyscrasias, constipation, hyper ureacemia, gynaecomastia, anorexia, hallucinations, impaired hepatic functions.'),
(343, 'Spiramycin', 'Respiratory tract infections, prostatitis, urethritis, impetigo, folliculitis. Toxoplasmosis in pregnant women. Children.', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Lactation.', 'Nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea and skin allergy.'),
(344, 'Oxtriphylline', 'Reversible airways obstruction.', 'Hypersensitivity. Status asthmaticus. Peptic ulcer, hypertension, liver, kidney and thyroid disorders. heart failure.', 'Pregnancy and breast feeding.', 'Tachycardia, restlessness.'),
(345, 'Niclosamide', 'Taenia saginata. Taenia solium. Diphyllobothrium latum, Hymenolepis nana. Threadworm.', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Digestion of the dead segments of injured T.Sodium can be hazardous, as the ova released from them may develop into larvae in the intestine, penetrate its wall and cause visceral cysticercosis, thus a thorough purge is essential. The scolex should be searched in the stools to be sure that the worm will not grow again.', 'GI upset, pruritus. Malaise and light headedness.'),
(346, 'Orlistat', 'Obesity.', 'Hypersensitivity. Chronic malabsorption syndrome. Cholestasis. Pregnancy, elderly and children.', 'Multi vitamin and micro nutrient supplementation during the course of treatment. History of hyperoxaluria or Ca oxalate nephrolithiasis. DM.', 'Faecal urgency and incontinence, flatulence, fatty stolls or discharge, headache, anxiety, fatigue, menstrual irrgularities, abdominal pain/discomfort.'),
(347, 'Cetrimide', 'Skin disinfection.', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Avoid contact with eyes; avoid use in body cavities.', 'Skin irritation and occasionally sensitization.'),
(348, 'Levobunolol', 'Indicated for lowering intraocular pressure in chronic open angle glaucoma and ocular hypertension.', 'Bronchial asthma/severe chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, sinus bradycardia, second and third degree AV block, overt cardiac failure, cardiogenic shock. Hypersensitivity Pregnancy, lactation and paediatrics age group.', 'In patients with non-allergic bronchospasm. Patients of diabetes mellitus who are concurrently receiving insulin or oral hypoglycaemic agents. Patients at risk of developing hypoglycaemia. Thyrotoxicosis. Cerebrovascular insufficiency.', 'Transient ocular burning and stinging, decrease in heart rate and blood pressure, urticaria pruritus, decreased corneal sensitivity. Iridocyclitis, headache, transient ataxia, dizziness and lethargy. Lethargy, decreased corneal sensitivity, tearing, visual disturbances, urticaria and pruritus.'),
(349, 'Flavoxate', 'Is indicated in urinary fequency, urgency and dysuria associated with lower urinary tract infection. Nocturia', 'Pyloric or duodenal obstruction, obstructive intestinal lesions or ileus, achalasia, gastrointestinal hemorrhage and obstructive uropathies of the lower urinary tract Contraindicated below the age of twelve years. GI haemorrhage or obstructive uropathies of the lower urinary tract, myasthenia gravis, severe ulceratice colitis, toxic megacolon.', 'Drowsiness, blurred vision. May affect ability to drive or operate machinery. May worsen hyperthyroidism, coronary artery dsease, congestive heart failure, prostatic hypertrophy, arrhythmias, tachycardia. autonomic neuropathy, hiatus hernia with reflux esophagitis, hepatic and renal impairment. Pregnancy, Lactation and elderly.', 'Nausea, vomiting, dry mouth, vertigo, headache, mental confusion, tachycardia and palpitation. Increased intraocular pressure, difficulty in ocular accommodation, blurred vision, nervousness, fatigue, hypersensitivity, dysuria, hyperpyrexia, eosinophilia, leukopenia, abdominal pain, constipation and difficulty in concentrating.'),
(350, 'Human Monoclonal anti-Rho-D Ig', 'Prevention of development of Anti-D antibodies in Rh negative mothers after child birth. For immunosuppression in organ transplantation. Autoimmune purpura.', 'Hypersensitivity to blood products. Rh-o(D) positive or D-u positive. Rh-o(D) negative or D-u negative patient.', 'Concomitant administration of live vaccines.', 'Increased risk of bacterial, fungal, viral (especially CMV) as well as opportunistic infections. Development of lymphomas and related malignancies after a long latency.'),
(351, 'Rubbella Vaccine', 'For immunization against German measles in girls from one year age to puberty mostly as combined MMR vaccine.', 'Pregnancy, febrile illness and in untreated tuberculosis.', 'Simultaneous administration of immunoglobulin.', 'Fever, malaise, sore throat, joint pain and lymphadenopathy.'),
(352, 'Cholecalciferol', 'Managing hypocalcemia in patients undergoing dialysia for chronic renal failure. Renal osteodystrophy. Hypocalaemia and Hyperphosphataemia. Vitamin D dependent rickets, renal tubular osteomalacia.', 'Hypercalcemia, evidence of Vitamin D toxicity, malabsorption syndrome, hypervitaminosis D, abnormal sensitivity to the effects of Vitamin D, decreased renal function. Contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation.', 'Pediatric doses must be individualized and monitored under close medical supervision, Idiopathic hypercalcemia, renal function impairment. Coronary disease renal function impairment and arteriosclerois, especially in the elderly. Hypoparathyroidism.', 'Dry mouth, muscle pain, polydipsia, anorexia, reversible azotemia, vomiting, pancreatitis, mild acidosis, metallic taste, rhinorrhea.'),
(353, 'Hydroxyprogestrone Caproate', 'As contraceptive. Hormone replacement therapy (HRT). Dysfunctional uterine bleeding. Endrometriosis. Premenstrual syndrome/tension. Threatened/habitual abortion. Endometrial carcinoma. Dysmenorrhea. Suppression of postpartum lactation. Hypoventilation.', 'Hypersensitivity.Undiagnosed vaginal bleeding, breast cancer, pregnancy, lactation. Thromboembolic disorders. History of seizures. Markedly impaired liver functions.', 'Diabetes. Exclude pregnancy. Suspicion of thromboembolic disorders.', 'Breast engorgement, headache, rise in body temperature, edema, esophageal reflux, acne and mood swings may occur. Irregular bleeding or amenorrhoea. Long term use of progestin in HRT may increase the risk of breast cancer. Blood sugar may rise and diabetes may be precipitated by long-term use of potent agents like levonorgestrel. Given in early pregnancy, progestins can cause masculinization of female foetus and other congenital abnormalities.'),
