(454, 'Ramipril', 'Hypertension and congestive heart failure. Prophylaxis of CV events in high-risk patients.', 'Hypersensitivity, bilateral renal artery stenosis, pregnancy, lactation, concurrent of K sparing diuretics. Aortic stenosis or outflow tract obstruction.', 'Hypovolaemia, hyperkalaemia, valvular stenosis, hypertension, elderly. PVD.', 'Hypotension, renal impairment, angioedema, chronic cough, hyperkalemia. Nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea, dizziness, fatigue, headache, abdominal pain.'),
(455, 'Mosapride', 'Disorders associated with decreased GI motility.', 'Hypersensitivity. Pregnancy. Patients in whom GI stimulation might be dangerous e.g. GI haemorrhage, mechanical obstruction or perforation.', 'Elderly, pregnancy, lactation and children. Renal and hepatic impairment.', 'Diarrhoea, dry mouth, malaise, abdominal pain, constipation.'),
(456, 'Desogestrel', 'III generation progesterone main progesterone activity and very little if any androgenic activity. As contraceptive. Hormone replacement therapy (HRT). Dysfunctional uterine bleeding. Endrometriosis. Premenstrual syndrome/tension. Threatened/habitual abortion. Endometrial carcinoma. Dysmenorrhea. Suppression of postpartum lactation. Hypoventilation.', 'Hypersensitivity.Undiagnosed vaginal bleeding, breast cancer, pregnancy, lactation. Thromboembolic disorders. History of seizures. Markedly impaired liver functions.', 'Diabetes. Exclude pregnancy. Suspicion of thromboembolic disorders.', 'Breast engorgement, headache, rise in body temperature, edema, esophageal reflux, acne and mood swings may occur. Irregular bleeding or amenorrhoea. Long term use of progestin in HRT may increase the risk of breast cancer. Blood sugar may rise and diabetes may be precipitated by long-term use of potent agents like levonorgestrel. Given in early pregnancy, progestins can cause masculinization of female foetus and other congenital abnormalities.'),
(457, 'Nitrofurantoin', 'Urinary tract infections.', 'Hypersensitivity. Impaired renal function. Pregnancy and neonates. Severe oliguria or anuria. G6PD deficiency.', 'Elderly. Pre-existing pulmonary, hepatic, neurological or allergic disorders. DM, electrolyte imbalance, debility, Vit B deficiency. Lactation.', 'Nausea, vomiting, anorexia, abdominal pain, diarrhoea, headache, vertigo, rash, urticaria, lupus-like syndrome, haemolytic anaemia. Peripheral polyneuropathy, hepatotoxicity, anaphylaxis. interstitial pneumonitis.'),
(458, 'Sertraline', 'Depression. Obsessive compulsive disorder. Panic disorder. Premenstrual dysphoric disorder.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hepatic impairment. Children below the age of eighteen years. Poorly controlled epilepsy.', 'Renal impairment. Alcoholism. Recent MI, history of bleeding disorders, DM and angle-closure glaucoma.', 'Dry mouth, nausea, stomach upset, diarrhoea, tremor, sweating, dizziness, sleeplessness, indigestion, paraesthesia, decreased libido, rash, hot flushes, blurred vision.'),
(459, 'Hyoscine', 'Gastric and duodenal ulcers, gastro intestinal spasm and hypermotility, pylorospasm in infants, nausea and vomiting, spastic constipation, biliary dyskinesia and spasm of the urinary tract, delayed relaxation of the lower uterine segment, dysmenorrhoea. Motion sickness.', 'Glaucoma. Retention of urine (Prostate hypertrophy). Mechanical Stenosis in the region of GIT. Tachycardia. Megacolon. Acute haemorrhage, paralytic ileus, cardiac insufficiency, myasthenia gravis.', 'Hepatic/renal disease, pyloric stenosis, urinary retention, prostatic hyperplasia, psychosis, seizure disorders, ulcerative colitis, coronary artery disease, tachyarrhythmias, heart failure, hypertension. Elderly, children, pregnancy and lactation.', 'Increased pulse rate, vision disturbances due to IV administration. Tremor, weakness, impaired accommodation, blurred vision, cycloplegia.'),
(460, 'Iron III Polymaltose', 'Iron deficiency either due to chronic blood loss or poor absorption.', 'Iron intolerance.', 'History peptic ulcer, severe renal failure. Iron and tetracycline bind together leading to impairment of absorption.', 'GI upset, black stools, abdominal discomfort or pain by oral therapy.'),
(461, 'Prulifoxacin', 'Urinary tract infections, community acquired respiratory tract infections gastroenteritis.', 'Anamnesis of tendon disease, hypersensitivity, coeliac disease, pregnancy, laction and epilepsy. Children.', 'Exposure to ultraviolet rays, glucose 6 phosphate dehydrogenase deficiency.', 'Panic disorders, psychosis, epilepsy, cardio respiratory insufficiency, hypersensitivity, sportaneous tendon rupture, prolongation of QT interval.'),
(462, 'Homatropine Methyl Bromide', 'Used in eye as mydriatic drug. On installation in eye it acts in 45-60 minutes, mydriasis lasts 1-3 days while accommodation recovers in 1-2 days.', 'Darkly pigmented lris is more resistant to pupillary dilatation and caution should be exercised to avoid over dosage. Mydriasis can precipitate acute angle-closure glaucoma in a few patients', 'Examination of fundus of eye in persons aged over 60 years or hypermetropic.', 'It often produces unsatisfactory cycloplegia in children who have high ciliary muscle tone.'),
(463, 'Amoxycillin Sodium', 'Respiratory, genito-urinary, skin and soft tissue, ENT infections due to susceptible strains of Gram negative organisms like H.influenzae, E-coli, P.mirabilis and N. gonorrhoea. Gram positive organisms like streptococci (including streptococcus faecalis) D. pneumoniae and non-penicillase producing staphylococci.', 'Individuals with a history of an allergic reactions to the penicillins. Contraindicated during pregnancy.', 'Periodic assessment of renal, hepatic and haematopoietic functions should be made during prolonged therapy. In case of super added infections with mycotic or bacterial pathogens (usually Enteobacter, Pseudomonas or Candida) the drug should be discontinued.', 'Nausea, vomiting and diarrhoea. Urticaria, skin rashes and serum sickness. Rise in SGOT. Anemia, thrombocytopenic purpura, eosinophilia, leukopenia and agranulocytosis.'),
(464, 'Ethamsylate IP', 'Prevention and treatment of capillary haemorrhages associated with (i) Haematemesis, melena, haemoptysis, haematuria, epitaxis (ii) menorrhagia, metrorrhagia, post-abortion and post-partum haemorrhages', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Patient with acute porphyria.', 'Headache, rash, nausea. Trasient hypotension with i.v. injection.'),
(465, 'Ephedrine', 'Mild chronic bronchial asthma. Epidural anaesthesia-induced hypotension.', 'Hypersensitivity. Hypertension, thyrotoxicosis, BPH, lactation.', 'Ischaemia heart disease, hyperthyroidism, diabetes mellitus, hypertension, angle-closure glaucoma, renal impairment, prostatic enlargement. Pregnancy, elderly.', 'Anxiety, tachycardia, tremor, dry mouth, hypertension, cardiac arrhythmias, impaired circulation to the extremities, nervousness, insomnia, palpitations. Difficulty in micturition in patients with prostatic enlargement. Cardiac arrhythmias.'),
(466, 'Hydroxy Progesterone Caproate IP', 'As contraceptive. Hormone replacement therapy (HRT). Dysfunctional uterine bleeding. Endrometriosis. Premenstrual syndrome/tension. Threatened/habitual abortion. Endometrial carcinoma. Dysmenorrhea. Suppression of postpartum lactation. Hypoventilation.', 'Hypersensitivity.Undiagnosed vaginal bleeding, breast cancer, pregnancy, lactation. Thromboembolic disorders. History of seizures. Markedly impaired liver functions.', 'Diabetes. Exclude pregnancy. Suspicion of thromboembolic disorders.', 'Breast engorgement, headache, rise in body temperature, edema, esophageal reflux, acne and mood swings may occur. Irregular bleeding or amenorrhoea. Long term use of progestin in HRT may increase the risk of breast cancer. Blood sugar may rise and diabetes may be precipitated by long-term use of potent agents like levonorgestrel. Given in early pregnancy, progestins can cause masculinization of female foetus and other congenital abnormalities.');
