(467, 'Beclomethasone', 'Atopic eczema. Allergic contact dermatitis. Lichen simplex. Primary irritant dermatitis. Seborrheic dermatitis. Psoriasis of face, flexures. Varicose eczema. Cystic acne. Alopecia areata. Discoid LE. Hypertrophied scars, keloids. Lichen planus. Nail disorders. Psoriasis of palm, sole, elbow, knee. A combination of steroid with proper antibiotic cover may also be used for: Impetigo, furunculosis, secondary infected dermatoses, napkin rash, otitis externa, intertriginous eruptions.', 'Hypersensitivity. Rosacea or perioral dermatitis. Primary infective skin. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Infants. Secondary dermatological infections.', 'Thinning of epidermis. Dermal changes - atrophy. Telangiectasia, Striae. Easy bruising, Hypopigmentation. Delayed wound healing. Fungal and bacterial infections. Systemic adverse effects of topical steroids on prolong use: Adrenal pituitary suppression. Cushings syndrome.'),
(468, 'Clomiphene', 'Female infertility, irregularly, ovulating women, menstrual cycle with a short luteal phase, oligomenorrhoea, dysfunctional uterine bleeding, amenorrhoea, post pill amenorrhoea, Steinleventhal syndrome, Chiari Frommel syndrome. Men: Oligospermia, asthenospermia.', 'Liver dysfunction, abnormal bleeding of undetermined origin, neoplastic diseases of genital tract. Pregnancy.', 'Exclude abnormal ovarian enlargement, exclude pregnancy.', 'Abdominal discomfort, ovarian enlargement, visual blurring, menopausal hot flushes, nausea, vomiting, dizziness, breast tenderness, heavier menses, intermenstrual spotting, urticaria, hair loss.'),
(469, 'Dopamine', 'Hemodynamic imbalance present in shock syndome caused by hepovolaemia, myocardial infarction, trauma, endotoxemia, septicaemia, open heart surgery, acute renal failure and chronic cardiac decompensation in congestive failure.', 'Pheochromocytoma, uncorrected tachycardia, ventricular fibrillation and hyperthyroidism. Hypersensitivity.', 'Shock secondary to MI, history of peripheral vascular disease. Correct hypovolaemia before infusion. History of occlusive vascular disease e.g. atherosclerosis, Raynauds disease, Buergers disease, diabetic endarteritis, disproportionate increase in diastolic pressure. Pregnancy.', 'Nausea, vomiting, anginal pain, dyspnoea, headache widened QRS complexes, azotaemia.'),
(470, 'Ethamsylate BP', 'Prevention and treatment of capillary haemorrhages associated with (i) Haematemesis, melena, haemoptysis, haematuria, epitaxis (ii) menorrhagia, metrorrhagia, post-abortion and post-partum haemorrhages', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Patient with acute porphyria.', 'Headache, rash, nausea. Trasient hypotension with i.v. injection.'),
(471, 'Meropenem', 'Nosocomial infections like septicaemia, febrile neutropenia, intraabdominal and pelvic infections, etc. caused by cephalosporin-resistant bacteria. For P aeruginosa infections, it should be combined with an aminoglycoside.', 'Hypersensitivity to ingredients. Hypersensitivity to penicillins or other beta-lactam antibiotics. Pseudomembranous colitis.', 'Infants below three month, renal insufficiency, neurological disorders, pregnancy and lactation.', 'Allergic reaction, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea, pseudomembranous colitis. Eosinophilia, thrombocytopenia and leucopenia. Headache, paresthesia, convulsions, oral and vaginal candidiasis.'),
(472, 'Testosterone Decancate', 'Testicular failure. Hypopituitarism. AIDS related muscle wasting. Hereditary angioneurotic edema. Ageing.', 'Hypersensitivity. Prostate and male breast carcinoma. Pregnancy and lactation. Hypercalcaemia or hypercalciuria.', 'Cardiovascular disorders, skeletal metastases, renal or hepatic impairment, epilepsy, migraine, diabetes. Elderly, prepubertal boys.', 'Virilization, excess body hair and menstrual irregularities in women. Acne. Frequent, sustained and often painful erections in males in the beginning of therapy, subside spontaneously after sometime. Oligozoospermia. Precocious puberty and shortening of stature. Edema. Cholestatic jaundice. Hepatic carcinoma. Gynaecomastia. Lowering of HDL and rise in LDL levels.'),
(473, 'Memantine', 'Treatment of moderate to severe dementia of the Alzheimers type.', 'Hypersensitivity.', 'Conditions that raise urine pH may decrease the urinary elimination of memantine resulting in increased plasma levels of memantine.', 'Fatique, pain, dizziness, headache, vomiting, back pain, coughing, dyspnea constipation, confusion, somnolence, hypertention.'),
