(512, 'Dimercaprol', 'Poisoning due to arsenic, mercury, gold, bismuth, nickel, thalium, antimony. As an adjuvant to calcium disodium edetate in lead poisoning. As an adjuvant to penicillamine in Cu poisoning and in wilsons disease.', 'Iron and cadmium poisoning.', 'Hypertension, hepatic damage. Antihistaminics give 1/2 hours,, before reduces intensity of adverse effects.', 'Rise in BP, tachycardia, vomiting, tingling and burning sensation, inflammation of mucous membranes, sweating, cramps, headache and anxiety.'),
(513, 'Diltiazem', 'Angina pectoris due to coronary artery spasm. Chronic stable angina, PSVTachyarrhythmias.', 'Sick-sinus syndrome, 2nd or 3rd degree AV block, porphyria. Severe congestive cardiac failure, marked bradycardia. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Elderly, hepatic or renal impairment, impaired left ventricular function, prolonged AV periods. Diabetics Melitus, hypotension.', 'Headache, nausea, dizziness, ankle oedema, hypotension, fatigue, flushig, GI discomfort, gingival hyperplasia, rashes, erythema multiforme, exfoliative dermatitis, photosensitivity, occasionally hepatitis. AV block, bradycardia, asystole, sinus arreast'),
