(522, 'Buspirone', 'Short term management of anxiety disorders and the relief of symptoms of anxiety with or without accompanying depression.', 'Hypersensitivity. Epilepsy. Severe renal and hepatic disease. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'History of renal or hepatic impairment. Alcoholism.', 'Dizziness, headache, nervousness, light headedness, excitement and nausea. Rarely tachycardia, palpitations, chest pain, drowsiness, confusion, dry mouth, fatigue, sweating.'),
(523, 'Amoxycillin', 'Respiratory, genito-urinary, skin and soft tissue, ENT infections due to susceptible strains of Gram negative organisms like H.influenzae, E-coli, P.mirabilis and N. gonorrhoea. Gram positive organisms like streptococci (including streptococcus faecalis) D. pneumoniae and non-penicillase producing staphylococci.', 'Individuals with a history of an allergic reactions to the penicillins. Contraindicated during pregnancy.', 'Periodic assessment of renal, hepatic and haematopoietic functions should be made during prolonged therapy. In case of super added infections with mycotic or bacterial pathogens (usually Enteobacter, Pseudomonas or Candida) the drug should be discontinued.', 'Nausea, vomiting and diarrhoea. Urticaria, skin rashes and serum sickness. Rise in SGOT. Anemia, thrombocytopenic purpura, eosinophilia, leukopenia and agranulocytosis.'),
