(526, 'Homotropine Methylbromide', 'Used in eye as mydriatic drug. On installation in eye it acts in 45-60 minutes, mydriasis lasts 1-3 days while accommodation recovers in 1-2 days.', 'Darkly pigmented lris is more resistant to pupillary dilatation and caution should be exercised to avoid over dosage. Mydriasis can precipitate acute angle-closure glaucoma in a few patients', 'Examination of fundus of eye in persons aged over 60 years or hypermetropic.', 'It often produces unsatisfactory cycloplegia in children who have high ciliary muscle tone.'),
(527, 'Roxithromycin', 'Respiratory tract infections. Caused by Streptococcal pharyngitis, pneumococci and H.influenzae. Prophylaxis of rheumatic fever and SABE. Diphtheia, Tetanus, syphilis and gonorrhoea. Infections caused by, Branh, catarrhalis, Gard. vagindalis, legionella and B. pertussis.', 'Hypersensitivity. Porphyria.', 'Hepatic insufficiency. Arrhythmias.', 'Nausea, vomiting, gastralgia, diarrhoea. Rarely rashes, hepatic impairment. Headache, dizziness, weakness, changes in blood counts, eosinophilia and acute pancreatitis.'),
