(701, 'Diethyl Carbamazine Citrate', 'W.bancroftii, B malayi. Tropical eosinophilia. Loa loa and O volvulus infections can also be treated.', 'Pregnancy.', 'Fall in BP may occur due to mass destruction of microfilariae and adult worms. The reaction can be minimized by starting with a low dose, and by giving antihistaminics or corticosteroids at the time of starting the treatment. Renal impairment.', 'Nausea, loss of appetite, headache, weakness, dizziness, rash, pruritus, enlargement of lymphnodes.');
