(1019, 'Galantamine', 'Mild to moderate Alzheimers disease. Dementia syndrome.', 'Hypersensitivity. Severe kidney and liver problem. Contraindicated during pregnancy and lactation. Contraindicated to paediatrics.', 'Use with caution in patients with Asthma, epilepsy, slow and irregular heart beat, stomach ulcer, urinary tract blockage or difficult urination. Take plenty of fluids during treatment. Dose adjustment is needed in liver and kidney problems.', 'Diarrhoea, nausea, anorexia and weight loss are the bothersome side effects. Less common side effects are chest pain or discomfort and shortness of breath.');
