(1238, 'Quinine Sulphate', 'Malaria: a) Uncomplicated resistant faciparum malaria. b) Complicated and severe malaria including cerebral malaria. Nocturnal muscle cramps. Varicose.', 'Hypersensitivity, haemolytic anaemia, quinine-resistant falciparum infection. Pregnancy, lactation. Tinnitus or optic neuritis. Myasthenia gravis. Prolonged QT interval.', 'Arterial fibrillation. Renal or hepatic impairment. CV diseases. G6PD deficiency. Diabetes mellitus.', 'Tinnitus. Impaired hearing, headache, blurred vision, vomiting, diarrhoea, abdominal pain, vertigo. Urticaria, pruritus, fever, angioedema, asthma, dyspnoea, haemoglobinuria, thrombocytopenic purpura, hypolgycaemia, renal failure, hypoprothrombinaemia, agranulocytosis.'),
