(1257, 'Disopyramide', 'Supraventricular and ventricular arrhythmias.', 'Patients with complete heart block, glaucoma, predisposition to urinary retention, myasthenia gravis. Sinus node disease in absence of pacemaker. Cardiomyopathy, Cardiogenic shock. Hypotention. Hypersensitivity. Children.', 'Conduction disorders or uncompensated heart failure. Pregnancy and lactation. Renal and hepatic failure. Family history of glaucoma. Correct K deficiency.', 'Impotence, constipation, difficulty in micturition, dry mouth, blurred vision, nausea, bloating, abdominal pain, vomiting, diarrhoea, colic. Psychosis, depression, skin rashes, dizziness, fatigue, muscle weakness, headache, cholestatic jaundice, elevated liver enzymes, thrombocytopenia, agranulocytosis, ventricular tachcardia and fibriliation, heart failure, hypotension, conduction disturbances. Urinary retention, severe CV depression if given as rapid IV Inj. High risk of recurrence of failure in patients with history of congestive cardiac failure. Negative inotropic effect esp prominent in patients with cardiomyopathy, HTN and uncompensated cardiac failure.'),
