(1266, 'Paroxetine', 'Depression. Obsessive compulsive disorders. Panic disorders. Anxiety. Posttraumatic stress disorder. Premenstrual dysmorphic disorder.', 'Concomitant use in patients taking monoamine oxidase inhibitors (MAOIS).', 'History of mania and seizures. Close supervision of high risk patients with suicidal tendencies. Severe renal or hepatic impairment. Avoid operating hazardous machinery, including automobiles. Glaucoma, history of mania, cardiac disease, DM, history of bleeding disorders.', 'Asthenia, sweating, nausea,decreased appetite, somnolence, dizziness, insomnia, tremor, nervousness. Constipation, ejaculatory disturbance and impotence. Pain, myoclonus, myopathy, myasthenia, arthralgia, blurred vision.'),
(1267, 'Bromocriptine Mesylate', 'Parkinsons disease. Hyperprolactinemia due to microprolactinomas causing galactorrhoea, amenorrhoea and infertility in women, gyanecomastia, impotence and sterility in men. Prevention of physiological lactation.', 'Hypersensitivity to ergot alkaloids.', 'Patients driving vehicles or operating heavy machinery. Cardiovascular, hepatic and renal impairment. Peptic ulcer, diabetes, diabetic retinopathy. Concurrent use of oral contraceptives. History of psychotic disorders. It should always be started at a low dose and then gradually increased till response occurs or side effects become limiting. Psychiatric disturbances are reported. Instead of oral only mechanical contraceptive measures should be employed. Discontinue if conception, peptic ulceration, diabetes, diabetic retinopathy, hepatic or renal dysfunction, severe cardiovascular disease occurs. Pituitary adenoma - evaluate sella turcica before initiating therapy.', 'Nausea,Vomiting, constipation, postural hypotension, syncope, behavioural alterations, mental confusion, hallucinations, psychosis.'),
(1268, 'Acetyl Salicylic Acid', 'Prophylaxis in cases of increased risk of blood clotting. Myocardial infarction, coronary bypass, transluminal angioplasty, strokes, transient ischaemic attack. Analgesic (Headache, backache, myalgia, joint pain, toothache, neuralgias, dysmenorrhoea). Antipyretic.', 'Hypersensitivity, haemophilia, hypoprothrombinaemia, platelet disorders, active peptic ulceration and other bleeding disorders. Children suffering from chicken pox or influenza. Avoided in diabetics and injuvenile rheumatoid arthritis and should be stopped before surgery. Contraindicated during pregnancy. Contraindicated below the age of twelve years.', 'May precipitate bronchospasm and induce asthmatic attacks in susceptible subjects. Gastrointestinal haemorrhage. Gout.', 'G.I. discomfort, nausea, vomiting. Epigastric distress, occult blood loss in stools, dizziness, tinnitus, vertigo, impairment of hearing and vision, excitement and mental confusion, hyperventilation and electrolyte imbalance. Drug interaction following concurrent use of aspirin with heparin, coumarin or corticoid derivatives, methotrexate, sulfonylureas, probenecid and sulfinpyrazone and spironolactone. It potentiates antiplatelet action of dipridamole.'),
(1269, 'Isoxsuprine', 'Premature labor, threatened or habitual abortion. Cerebral and peripheral vascular disease.', 'Presence of recent aterial haemorrhage. Acute coronary thrombosis.', 'Severe angina pectoris. Hyperthyroidism, recent myocardial lesion, paroxysmal tachycardia. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Dizziness, nausea, vomiting, hypertension, palpitation, rash, abdominal disturbances, hypotension. Maternal pulomary oedema and foetal tachycardia (IV).'),
(1270, 'Mefloquine', 'Used as a second line treatment in chloroquine resistant malaria, severe malaria due to P. falciparum and P-vivax including cerebral malaria.', 'Hypersensitivity. History psychiatric illness and seizure disorders. Lactation. Severe hepatic and renal impairment.', 'Should be used during pregnancy only if the potential benefits justifies the potential risk to the foetus.', 'Nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, diarrhoea, dysphoria, dizziness, headache, sleep disorders, vertigo, neuropsychiatric reactions, bradycardia, visual/auditory disturbances, pruritus, sialorrhea, arthralgia and fatigue, syncope, extrasystole. Seizures, thrombocytopenia, leucopenia. AV block, encephalopathy.'),
